dfischer.utils

Class PerformanceDataSnapshot

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.PerformanceDataSnapshot

  • public class PerformanceDataSnapshot
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains a statistic snapshot, collected on a "sampling interval" during the load test (time based sampling).
    See Also:
    PerformanceData.getSnapshots()

      • getActualSessionTime

        public long getActualSessionTime()
        Returns the latest (most actual) time of one loop per concurrent user. This includes the all response times of all URLs and all page break delays.

        Caution: the result is not valid if not at least one loop has been completed successful. Please check this with getPassedLoops().

        Returns:
        the latest (most actual) time of one loop per concurrent user measured in milliseconds, or -1 if if no result is available
        See Also:
        getPassedLoops()

      • getAverageSessionTime

        public long getAverageSessionTime()
        Deprecated. since version 4.3-B - use getActualSessionTime().
        Returns:
        the total (average) time of one loop per concurrent user in milliseconds or -1 if if no result is available. Caution: the result is not valid if not at least one loop has been completed successful. Please check this with getPassedLoops().
        See Also:
        getActualSessionTime(), getPassedLoops()
